File: The home in Pinetown where four children were killed, reportedly by their father, on Tuesday. DURBAN - Four Pinetown siblings, who were killed, allegedly by their father, are being laid to rest on Sunday. The children, aged between four and sixteen, were murdered earlier in the week. The oldest child, a teenage girl, was strangled in the bushes while her siblings were all hanged in their home The 44-year-old accused has made his first appearance in court, where he abandoned bail application. He is due back in the dock on 9 October.